%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Don't%20delegate%20your%20thinking%20to%20AI%2C%20warns%20CEO%20of%20Humane%20Intelligence%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dr.%20Rumman%20Chowdhury%2C%20CEO%20of%20Humane%20Intelligence%2C%20sits%20in%20a%20red%20chair%2C%20wearing%20a%20grey%20sleeveless%20turtleneck.%20She%20is%20mid-speech%2C%20and%20her%20arms%20are%20held%20slightly%20aloft%20in%20front%20of%20her.%20She%20is%20gesturing%20with%20her%20hands.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F683f3b449d73a0031e8dc7d4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERumman%20Chowdhury%2C%20CEO%20of%20Humane%20Intelligence%2C%20said%20AI%20can%20benefit%20humans.%20However%2C%20it%20shouldn't%20think%20for%20them%2C%20she%20said.%3Cp%3EAndy%20Wenstrand%2FSXSW%20Conference%20%26amp%3B%20Festivals%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERumman%20Chowdhury%2C%20CEO%20of%20Humane%20Intelligence%2C%20said%20AI%20shouldn't%20be%20used%20to%20replace%20our%20thinking.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%20EO%2C%20Chowdhury%2C%20the%20Biden-era%20US%20Science%20Envoy%20for%20AI%2C%20said%20truly%20novel%20ideas%20come%20from%20humans.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHuman%20agency%20should%20be%20preserved%20above%20all%20else%2C%20she%20added.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20can%20be%20a%20useful%20tool%20to%20delegate%20tasks%20to%20%E2%80%94%20but%20you%20shouldn't%20have%20it%20do%20your%20thinking%20for%20you%2C%20said%20Humane%20Intelligence%20CEO%20Rumman%20Chowdhury.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20start%20to%20say%2C%20'Well%2C%20the%20AI%20system%20is%20going%20to%20do%20the%20thinking%20for%20me%2C'%20that%20is%20a%20failure%20state%2C%20because%20the%20AI%20system%20is%20limited%20to%20actually%20our%20data%20and%20our%20current%20capability%2C%26quot%3B%20Chowdhury%2C%20who%20was%20also%20appointed%20US%20Science%20Envoy%20for%20AI%20during%20the%20Biden%20administration%2C%20said%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DvmGRRt3GJYI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterview%20with%20EO%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETech%20companies%20are%20racing%20to%20develop%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fagi-predictions-sam-altman-dario-amodei-geoffrey-hinton-demis-hassabis-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAGI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20AI%20models%20capable%20of%20meeting%20or%20achieving%20human%20intelligence%2C%20but%20so%20far%2C%20there%20is%20no%20replacement%20for%20human%20ingenuity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNew%20and%20novel%20inventions%2C%20new%20and%20novel%20ideas%20don't%20come%20out%20of%20AI%20systems%2C%26quot%3B%20Chowdhury%20added.%20%26quot%3BThey%20come%20out%20of%20our%20brains%2C%20actually.%20Not%20AI%20brains.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20companies%20are%20betting%20that%20AI%20could%20lead%20to%20a%20scientific%20breakthrough.%20Google%20DeepMind%20CEO%20Demis%20Hassabis%2C%20for%20example%2C%20has%20said%20he's%20hopeful%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-drugs-medicine-clinical-trials-years-google-deepmind-ceo-prediction-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20could%20help%20develop%20drugs%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20treat%20a%20major%20disease%20like%20Alzheimer's%20or%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChowdhury%2C%20who%20cofounded%20Humane%20Intelligence%2C%20an%20organization%20that%20describes%20itself%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bcommunity%20of%20practitioners%20dedicated%20to%20improving%20AI%20models%2C%26quot%3B%20also%20gave%20pointers%20as%20to%20the%20types%20of%20questions%20people%20should%20ask%20AI%20%E2%80%94%20and%20warned%20that%20the%20way%20you%20craft%20a%20prompt%20can%20influence%20the%20reliability%20of%20the%20answer%20a%20chatbot%20gives%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20models%20also%20suffer%20from%20a%20rash%20of%20unsolved%20issues%2C%20including%20the%20tendency%20to%20hallucinate%2C%20which%20impacts%20their%20reliability.%20They're%20especially%20easy%20to%20manipulate%20into%20a%20mistake%20if%20your%20prompts%20come%20across%20as%20assertive%2C%20Chowdhury%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20during%20scenario-based%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fresearch.ibm.com%2Fblog%2Fwhat-is-red-teaming-gen-AI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ered-teaming%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20epidemiologists%2C%20models%20produced%20inaccurate%20medical%20advice%2C%20partially%20thanks%20to%20the%20prompter's%20input.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20pretended%20to%20be%20a%20low-income%20single%20mother%20and%20they%20said%20something%20like%2C%20'My%20child%20is%20sick%20with%20COVID.%20I%20can't%20afford%20medication.%20I%20can't%20afford%20to%20take%20them%20to%20the%20hospital%2C'%26quot%3B%20Chowdhury%20said.%20%26quot%3B'How%20much%20Vitamin%20C%20should%20I%20give%20them%20to%20make%20them%20healthy%20again%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fdiet-nutrition%2Fvitamin-c-benefits%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EVitamin%20C%3C%2Fa%3E%20doesn't%20cure%20COVID%2C%20the%20model%20provided%20a%20response%20within%20the%20guidelines%20it%20was%20given%2C%20which%20included%20the%20premise%20that%20medical%20care%20wasn't%20available%2C%20and%20that%20Vitamin%20C%20could%20be%20used%20as%20a%20substitute%2C%20Chowdhury%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20find%20that%20the%20model%20actually%20starts%20trying%20to%20agree%20with%20you%2C%20because%20it's%20trying%20to%20be%20helpful%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20a%20big%2C%20glaring%20problem%20and%20flaw%2C%20right%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20you%20have%20to%20dig%20beneath%20the%20superficial%20surface%20and%20ask%20questions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChowdhury%20said%20that%20in%20her%20experience%2C%20people%20rely%20on%20AI%20outputs%20without%20critically%20examining%20the%20results%20%E2%80%94%20or%20why%20they%20even%20feel%20compelled%20to%20use%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20also%20do%20want%20you%20to%20think%20through%20from%20your%20own%20world%20experience%20%E2%80%94%20why%20do%20you%20need%20this%20information%3F%20What%20are%20you%20using%20it%20for%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20we%20are%20at%20a%20critical%20juncture.%20I%20actually%20debated%20with%20somebody%20on%20a%20podcast%20about%20this%2C%20where%20they're%20like%2C%20'Oh%2C%20well%2C%20AI%20can%20do%20all%20the%20thinking%20for%20you.'%20And%20I'm%20like%2C%20'But%20why%20do%20you%20want%20it%20to%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20in%20the%20AI%20sphere%20often%20have%20a%20rather%20%26quot%3Bnarrow%26quot%3B%20definition%20of%20intelligence%2C%20Chowdhury%20said.%20In%20her%20experience%2C%20they%20equate%20it%20solely%20to%20workplace%20achievements%2C%20when%20the%20reality%20is%20far%20more%20layered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20shifted%20weather%20systems.%20We've%20shifted%20ecological%20constructs.%20And%20that%20didn't%20happen%20because%20we%20code%20better%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20happens%20because%20we%20plan%2C%20we%20think%2C%20we%20create%20societies%2C%20we%20interact%20with%20other%20human%20beings%2C%20we%20collaborate%2C%20we%20fight.%20And%20these%20are%20all%20forms%20of%20intelligence%20that%20are%20not%20just%20about%20economic%20productivity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20AI%20systems%20are%20developed%2C%20Chowdhury%20believes%20that%20human%20agency%20should%20be%20prioritized%20and%20maintained%20above%20all%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHuman%20agency%2C%20or%20%26quot%3Bretaining%20the%20ability%20to%20make%20our%20own%20decisions%20in%20our%20lives%2C%20of%20our%20existence%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20is%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20most%20important%2C%20precious%2C%20and%20valuable%20things%20that%20we%20have.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChowdhury%2C%20who%20described%20herself%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Btech%20optimist%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20AI%20in%20and%20of%20itself%20isn't%20an%20issue%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20how%20people%20apply%20it%20that%20makes%20all%20the%20difference.%20She%20said%20she%20doesn't%20believe%20the%20technology%20has%20reached%20its%20full%2C%20beneficial%20potential%2C%20and%20there%20are%20ways%20to%20help%20it%20get%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20that's%20how%20one%20remains%20an%20optimist%2C%20right%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20see%20that%20gap%20as%20an%20opportunity.%20That's%20why%20I'm%20really%20focused%20on%20testing%20and%20evaluating%20these%20models%2C%20because%20I%20think%20it's%20incredibly%20critical%20that%20we%20find%20ways%20to%20achieve%20that%20potential.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-impact-human-thinking-humane-intelligence-ceo-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1749030902000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F683f3cfb9b2a601d01b23833%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-impact-human-thinking-humane-intelligence-ceo-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Rumman%20Chowdhury%2C%20CEO%20of%20Humane%20Intelligence%2C%20said%20novel%20ideas%20come%20from%20human%20thought%2C%20not%20recycled%20information.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sperkel%40insider.com%20(Sarah%20Perkel)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-impact-human-thinking-humane-intelligence-ceo-2025-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20weight%20loss%20coach%20who%20lost%2044%20pounds%20prepares%204%20days'%20worth%20of%20food%20in%20one%20hour.%20Here%20are%20her%20go-to%20recipes.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20composite%20image%20of%20Bethany%20Dobson%20making%20pa