etween%20April%202020%20and%20July%202024%2C%20Florida%20saw%20a%20net%20gain%20of%20roughly%201.8%20million%20residents%2C%20according%20to%20Census%20Bureau%20estimates%2C%20consistently%20jockeying%20for%20the%20title%20of%20fastest-growing%20US%20state.%20Florida%20continued%20to%20welcome%20plenty%20of%20snowbirds%2C%20sure%2C%20but%20it%20also%20lured%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fa16z-expands-new-offices-miami-new-york-los-angeles-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eventure%20capitalists%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiami-florida-stock-market-crash-crypto-bubble-parties-real-estate-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecrypto%20speculators%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20pretty%20much%20anyone%20who%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflorida-gov-ron-desantis-lift-coronavirus-restrictions-statewide-2020-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esick%20of%20COVID%20restrictions%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20was%20just%20chasing%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-people-move-out-of-florida-housing-prices-insurance-weather-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bvacation%26quot%3B%20feel%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20one%20Business%20Insider%20headline%20read%20in%20late%202023%3A%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-are-people-moving-florida-home-prices-cost-of-living-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYoung%20people%20are%20flocking%20to%20Florida%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20those%20transplants%20needed%20places%20to%20live.%20The%20lower%20half%20of%20the%20US%2C%20otherwise%20known%20as%20the%20Sun%20Belt%2C%20has%20traditionally%20been%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-home-house-prices-rent-cost-decline-cheaper-cities-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehotbed%20of%20home%20construction%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20helping%20keep%20prices%20in%20check%20despite%20the%20region's%20population%20growth.%20But%20even%20by%20the%20Sun%20Belt's%20development-friendly%20standards%2C%20builders%20in%20Florida%20were%20busy.%20They%20completed%20more%20than%20760%2C000%20new%20homes%20between%20April%202020%20and%20July%202024%2C%20the%20census%20estimates%2C%20a%20nearly%208%25%20increase%20in%20the%20state's%20housing%20stock.%20Only%20five%20states%20saw%20bigger%20building%20booms%20on%20a%20percentage%20basis%2C%20though%20with%20the%20exception%20of%20Texas%2C%20all%20have%20far%20fewer%20residents%20than%20Florida.%20The%20Sunshine%20State%20is%20home%20to%20about%206.8%25%20of%20the%20nation's%20population%2C%20but%20it%20accounted%20for%20nearly%2012%25%20of%20new%20home%20construction%20permits%20issued%20last%20year%2C%20an%20analysis%20by%20Realtor.com%20found.%20In%20both%20Texas%20and%20Florida%2C%20homebuilding%20activity%20%26quot%3Bgot%20close%20to%20or%20exceeded%20subprime%2C%20crazy%20construction%20days%2C%26quot%3B%20Rick%20Palacios%20Jr.%2C%20the%20director%20of%20research%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjbrec.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJohn%20Burns%20Research%20and%20Consulting%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20tells%20me%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20heady%20times%20just%20before%20the%202008%20collapse.%20But%20even%20the%20most%20ambitious%20builders%20couldn't%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20influx%20of%20transplants%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsell-investment-property-stopped-being-landlord-put-money-in-market-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einvestors%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20vacation-home%20buyers%20in%20Florida.%20As%20more%20people%20angled%20for%20homes%2C%20prices%20soared.%20According%20to%20data%20from%20the%20real%20estate%20search%20portal%20Redfin%2C%20the%20median%20home%20price%20in%20Florida%20peaked%20at%20%24423%2C000%20in%20April%202024%2C%20up%2061%25%20from%20the%20onset%20of%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20those%20fresh%20arrivals%20eventually%20soured%20on%20paradise%2C%20though%3A%20too%20hot%2C%20too%20expensive%2C%20or%20just%20not%20home.%20Even%20a%20vacation%2C%20it%20turns%20out%2C%20can%20get%20a%20little%20old.%20And%20when%20lots%20of%20new%20housing%20supply%20hits%20just%20as%20buyer%20demand%20is%20waning%2C%20the%20stage%20is%20set%20for%20prices%20to%20drop%20%E2%80%94%20just%20ask%20builders%20in%20Texas.%20Last%20year%2C%20I%20wrote%20about%20the%20cooling%20of%20the%20Austin%20market%2C%20where%20home%20prices%20are%20now%20down%20about%2014%25%20from%20their%20peak%2C%20per%20Redfin.%20In%20many%20ways%2C%20the%20story%20there%20is%20repeating%20itself%20in%20Florida%3A%20A%20bunch%20of%20people%20moved%20in%2C%20home%20prices%20shot%20up%2C%20and%20builders%20responded%20by%20putting%20tons%20of%20shovels%20in%20the%20ground.%20Then%20interest%20rates%20jumped%2C%20home%20loans%20got%20more%20expensive%2C%20and%20buyer%20demand%20hit%20the%20skids.%20Cue%20the%20price%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%2C%20of%20course%2C%20some%20more%20Florida-specific%20factors%20at%20play.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretiree-bought-hurricane-proof-florida-house-in-hurricane-milton-path-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBack-to-back%20hurricanes%3C%2Fa%3E%20tore%20through%20its%20western%20coast%20late%20last%20year%2C%20adding%20to%20the%20existing%20home%20insurance%20quagmire.%20Premiums%20have%20skyrocketed%20in%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20and%20multiple%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhomeowners-california-florida-insurance-issues-natural-disasters-wildfires-hurricanes-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehome%20insurers%20have%20abandoned%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20state%20entirely.%20The%20average%20cost%20of%20home%20insurance%20in%20Florida%20climbed%2045%25%20from%202017%20to%202022%2C%20according%20to%20an%20analysis%20by%20the%20Florida%20Policy%20Project.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fabolish-hoas-homeowner-associations-housing-market-real-estate-costs-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESteep%20HOA%20fees%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20along%20with%20the%20hefty%20insurance%20outlays%2C%20have%20made%20it%20difficult%20for%20owners%20of%20aging%20condo%20units%20to%20offload%20their%20properties.%20Florida%20has%20also%20lost%20some%20of%20its%20luster%20among%20US%20movers.%20Four%20of%20its%20biggest%20metros%20%E2%80%94%20Tampa%2C%20Miami%2C%20Orlando%2C%20and%20Fort%20Lauderdale%20%E2%80%94%20were%20among%20the%2010%20areas%20around%20the%20country%20that%20saw%20the%20steepest%20dropoff%20in%20net%20domestic%20migration%20from%202023%20to%202024%2C%20Redfin%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20the%20about-face%20in%20Florida's%20housing%20market%20has%20put%20only%20a%20small%20dent%20in%20headline%20property%20values.%20Sales%20prices%20in%20Florida%20are%20down%20roughly%203%25%20from%20their%20high%20point%20in%20spring%202024%2C%20per%20Redfin%20%E2%80%94%20hardly%20even%20%26quot%3Bcorrection%26quot%3B%20territory%2C%20let%20alone%20a%20bust.%20But%20Florida%20could%20still%20have%20a%20ways%20to%20fall.%20Builders%20and%20agents%20in%20Texas%20%E2%80%94%20where%20the%20pandemic%20frenzy%20has%20cooled%20off%20considerably%20%E2%80%94%20seem%20to%20have%20found%20an%20equilibrium%2C%20Cara%20Lavender%2C%20a%20senior%20research%20manager%20at%20John%20Burns%2C%20tells%20me.%20Sure%2C%20they're%20selling%20fewer%20homes%20each%20month%2C%20but%20they've%20slashed%20prices%20enough%20that%20they're%20able%20to%20keep%20things%20moving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20feel%20like%20we've%20hit%20that%20point%20in%20Florida%2C%26quot%3B%20Lavender%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BThey%20haven't%20found%20the%20bottom.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapp.parcllabs.com%2Fmarkets%2Frankings%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EParcl%20Labs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20real%20estate%20analytics%20firm%2C%20recently%20looked%20at%20the%20supply%20and%20demand%20dynamics%20in%2042%20metros%20around%20the%20country%20to%20deliver%20a%20%26quot%3Bbullish%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bbearish%26quot%3B%20rating%20for%20each%20one%20%E2%80%94%20basically%2C%20whether%20they%20think%20prices%20will%20rise%20or%20fall%20over%20the%20next%20year.%20Miami%20and%20Jacksonville%20got%20positive%20ratings%2C%20but%20Orlando%2C%20Tampa%2C%20Lakeland%2C%20Deltona%2C%20North%20Port%2C%20and%20Cape%20Coral%20all%20got%20slapped%20with%20the%20bearish%20tag.%20The%20key%20in%20those%20places%2C%20Parcl's%20CEO%2C%20Trevor%20Bacon%2C%20tells%20me%2C%20is%20the%20number%20of%20homes%20sitting%20on%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20ton%20of%20supply%2C%26quot%3B%20Bacon%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BLike%2C%20a%20ridiculous%20amount%20of%20supply.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHomebuilders%20are%20an%20optimistic%20bunch%20by%20nature%2C%20but%20even%20the%20ones%20in%20Florida%20are%20now%20saying%20they%20expect%20to%20end%20the%20year%20down%20slightly%20on%20their%20prices.%20%26quot%3BFor%20a%20builder%20to%20even%20report%20in%20a%20survey%20that%20they're%20going%20to%20be%20negative%20year%20over%20year%20on%20pricing%20is%20incredibly%20meaningful%2C%26quot%3B%20Lavender%20says.%20During%20a%20call%20with%20analysts%20in%20late%20March%2C%20Jon%20Jaffe%2C%20the%20president%20and%20co-CEO%20of%20Lennar%2C%20one%20of%20the%20country's%20largest%20builders%2C%20said%20buyers%20in%20Florida%20and%20Texas%20generally%20needed%20more%20help%20than%20those%20in%20most%20other%20places%20around%20the%20country.%20Builders%20in%20the%20state%20are%20dropping%20prices%2C%20lending%20a%20hand%20on%20closing%20costs%2C%20and%20chipping%20in%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20to%20help%20buyers%20get%20lower%20mortgage%20rates%2C%20all%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20keep%20sales%20moving.%20Even%20then%2C%20Jaffe%20said%2C%20the%20company%20didn't%20see%20the%20typical%20pickup%20in%20nationwide%20sales%20that%20usually%20comes%20with%20the%20start%20of%20the%20spring%20selling%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20found%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-agents-realtors-reckoning-housing-market-home-sales-slow-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ereal%20estate%20agents%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20like%20builders%2C%20tend%20to%20see%20the%20sunny%20side%20of%20things%20%E2%80%94%20after%20all%2C%20it's%20pretty%20much%20their%20job%20to%20preach%20the%20gospel%20of%20homeownership%20even%20when%20the%20market%20is%20less%20than%20accommodating.%20But%20when%20I%20talked%20to%20Laurie%20Rose%2C%20a%20real%20estate%20agent%20and%20longtime%20resident%20of%20Naples%2C%20in%20southwest%20Florida%2C%20she%20was%20clear-eyed%20about%20the%20challenges%20facing%20buyers%20in%20her%20chosen%20state.%20Rose%20and%20her%20husband%20moved%20down%20from%20New%20Jersey%20in%202003%2C%20mostly%20for%20the%20weather.%20For%20a%20while%2C%20it%20felt%20like%20the%20move%20was%20paying%20off%3A%20Gas%20was%20cheaper%2C%20and%20groceries%20didn't%20stretch%20their%20budget.%20The%20lack%20of%20a%20state%20income%20tax%20kept%20more%20dollars%20in%20their%20pockets.%20Now%20everything%20is%20more%20expensive%2C%20she%20says%2C%20including%20everyday%20items%20like%20food%20and%20clothing.%20On%20the%20plus%20side%2C%20home%20values%20are%20way%20up%20since%20she%20and%20her%20husband%20bought%20their%20place.%20But%20even%20if%20they%20sold%2C%20she%20says%2C%20there's%20no%20way%20she%20could%20buy%20back%20into%20the%20area%20in%20which%20she's%20now%20living.%20Rose%20still%20says%20Florida%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bgreat%20place%20to%20live%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20the%20state's%20natural%20draws%20aren't%20always%20enough%20to%20keep%20people%20there.%20She%20tells%20me%20several%20of%20her%20friends%20have%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floved-nyc-moved-to-small-town-tenessee-save-money-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emoved%20to%20Tennessee%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Georgia%2C%20and%20the%20Carolinas%20in%20search%20of%20the%20cheaper%20living%20that%20Florida%20once%20promised.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERose's%20work%20as%20a%20real%20estate%20agent%20has%20also%20given%20her%20a%20front-row%20seat%20to%20the%20mounting%20challenges%20for%20both%20sellers%20and%20buyers%20in%20Florida.%20Buyers%20are%20leery%20of%20all%20the%20costs%20that%20come%20with%20homeownership%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20the%20higher%20mortgage%20rates%20and%20steep%20sticker%20prices%20that%20have%20eaten%20into%20affordability%2C%20but%20also%20the%20insurance%20premiums%2C%20property%20taxes%2C%20and%20HOA%20fees.%20With%20more%20homes%20sitting%20on%20the%20market%20and%20prices%20starting%20to%20drop%20from%20last%20year%2C%20there's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-now-good-time-to-buy-home-real-estate-agents-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eno%20rush%20among%20buyers%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20get%20in%20on%20the%20action.%20Sellers%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20will%20have%20to%20come%20to%20grips%20with%20this%20new%20state%20of%20play%20if%20they%20want%20to%20get%20their%20properties%20sold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSellers%20have%20been%20caught%20up%20in%20this%20thing%20of%2C%20'I%20can%20put%20whatever%20price%20I%20want%20on%20my%20home%2C%20and%20someone's%20going%20to%20buy%20it%2C'%26quot%3B%20Rose%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BNow%20all%20of%20a%20sudden%20they're%20going%3A%20'Oh%2C%20crap.%20People%20aren't%20buying%2C%20and%20people%20aren't%20even%20looking.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20just%20a%20Florida%20story.%20Large-scale%20housing%20trends%20often%20obscure%20the%20quirks%20that%20make%20each%20local%20market%20unique%2C%20Jake%20Krimmel%2C%20a%20senior%20economist%20at%20Realtor.com%2C%20tells%20me%2C%20but%20Florida%20offers%20a%20neat%20microcosm%20of%20the%20national%20numbers.%20Around%20the%20country%2C%20supply%20is%20back%20up%20to%20levels%20we%20haven't%20seen%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20handing%20more%20power%20to%20buyers%20who%20now%20have%20the%20luxury%20of%20choice%20(provided%20they%20can%20afford%20it).%20Homes%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-buying-a-home-mortgage-rates-prices-inventory-outlook-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esitting%20on%20the%20market%20longer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20sellers%20are%20coming%20around%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20they'll%20have%20to%20cut%20asking%20prices%20if%20they%20want%20to%20see%20some%20offers.%20The%20softness%20in%20Florida's%20market%20appears%20to%20be%20spreading%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20Southeast%20and%20Southwest%2C%20where%20metros%20such%20as%20Phoenix%2C%20Denver%2C%20Atlanta%2C%20and%20Raleigh%20now%20show%20negative%20prices%20year%20over%20year%20in%20John%20Burns'%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Southeast%20and%20the%20Southwest%20aren't%20as%20weak%20as%20Texas%20and%20Florida%20right%20now%2C%20but%20they%20could%20very%20well%20be%20on%20their%20way%20there%20if%20supply%20continues%20to%20increase%20and%20buyer%20demand%20stays%20where%20it%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20Lavender%20tells%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20want%20to%20be%20clear%20that%20the%20sky%20isn't%20falling%20here.%20The%20pandemic-era%20frenzy%20couldn't%20last%20forever%2C%20and%20a%20pullback%20in%20demand%20was%20to%20be%20expected%20given%20just%20how%20many%20people%20bought%20and%20sold%20homes%20before%20rates%20went%20up%20in%202022.%20If%20builders%20hadn't%20delivered%20all%20that%20supply%20to%20Florida%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20the%20affordability%20picture%20there%20would%20be%20all%20the%20more%20dire.%20Just%20look%20at%20the%20Midwest%20and%20the%20Northeast%2C%20where%20fewer%20homes%20were%20built%20and%20the%20supply%20remains%20tight.%20They%20may%20not%20be%20seeing%20a%20drop%20in%20prices%20now%2C%20but%20that%20means%20buyers%20aren't%20getting%20any%20relief%2C%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlorida's%20growth%20during%20the%20pandemic%20was%20%26quot%3Bunsustainable%2C%26quot%3B%20Nelson%20Stabile%2C%20a%20principal%20and%20cofounder%20of%20the%20Miami-based%20development%20firm%20Integra%20Investments%2C%20tells%20me.%20But%20he's%20still%20a%20staunch%20believer%20in%20the%20state's%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20we're%20at%20a%20healthy%20pace%20now%2C%20and%20I%20think%20the%20whole%20country%20has%20woken%20up%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20Florida%20is%20not%20just%20a%20retirement%20destination%2C%26quot%3B%20Stabile%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20place%20where%20folks%20can%20raise%20their%20families%2C%20where%20they%20can%20have%20an%20incredible%20quality%20of%20life.%20Is%20it%20perfect%3F%20No.%20But%20is%20it%20better%20than%20most%20areas%3F%20Probably%2C%20yes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKeith%20Poliakoff%2C%20a%20real%20estate%20attorney%20in%20Florida%2C%20is%20similarly%20bullish%20on%20his%20state.%20But%20he%20also%20says%20other%20states%20should%20learn%20lessons%20from%20Florida's%20saga%20%E2%80%94%20to%20cut%20red%20tape%20that%20gets%20in%20the%20way%20of%20building%20affordable%20housing%2C%20as%20the%20state%20legislature%20recently%20did%20through%20the%20Live%20Local%20Act%2C%20and%20strengthen%20building%20codes%20to%20withstand%20climate%20disasters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFlorida%20generally%20hits%20the%20wave%20before%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20Poliakoff%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20good%20indicator%20of%20what's%20to%20come.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjames-rodriguez%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EJames%20Rodriguez%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20reporter%20on%20Business%20Insider's%20Discourse%20team.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on